longBusinessSummary: Reflex Advanced Materials Corp. engages in the exploration of mineral properties in Canada. The company explores in battery metals space. It has an option agreement to acquire 100% interests in the Ruby Graphite project covering approximately 2,000 acres and 96 federal lode mining claims located in Beaverhead County, Montana; and the Zig-Zag Lake Lithium Property that consists of eight mining claims totaling approximately 2,710 hectares located in Thunder Bay Mining Division, Crescent Lake Area, Ontario. The company was formerly known as Freedom Battery Metals Inc. and changed its name to Reflex Advanced Materials Corp. in October 2022. Reflex Advanced Materials Corp. was incorporated in 2021 and is based in Vancouver, Canada.
